A lot of the static data endpoints don't return all the data by default, so you will have to specifically request it using the ChampData/SpellData/ItemData parameter.

For example, the champion endpoint will only return basic information such as champion name, key, id and title.

When you use the overloaded method **getDataChampionList(Region)** without the ChampData parameter, you will just get this default information, and everything else will be 0-false-null.

If you want information like image, skin, or lore data, you will have to use **getDataChampionList(locale, version, dataById, champData)**, providing the kind of ChampData you want to the champData parameter.

Here is an example, printing out all the skin names of each champion:

``` java
import net.rithms.riot.api.RiotApi;
import net.rithms.riot.api.RiotApiException;
import net.rithms.riot.constant.Region;
import net.rithms.riot.constant.staticdata.ChampData;
import net.rithms.riot.dto.Static.Champion;
import net.rithms.riot.dto.Static.ChampionList;
import net.rithms.riot.dto.Static.Skin;

public class Example {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws RiotApiException {
        // TODO Auto-generated method stub
        RiotApi api = new RiotApi("API-KEY", Region.NA);
        ChampionList championList = api.getDataChampionList(null, null, false, ChampData.SKINS);
        for(Champion champion : championList.getData().values()) {
            System.out.println(champion.getName());
            for(Skin skin : champion.getSkins()) {
                System.out.println(skin.getName());
            } System.out.println("======");
        } 
    }
}
```

Note you can provide multiple ChampData values, or can use **ChampData.ALL** if you want to receive all data.

