The default `addr` is located in `src/cmd/server.rs`
```
pub fn get_cmd(matches: &ArgMatches) -> Cmd {
    Cmd {
        addr: matches.value_of("addr").unwrap_or("127.0.0.1:4000").to_string(),
        edit: matches.is_present("edit"),
    }
}
```

So a typical request would be made against `127.0.0.1:4000/json-rpc` with a payload of the [json-rpc](http://www.jsonrpc.org/specification) specification. The only supported "method" is currently "GetArtifacts" which does not accept any "params".

